[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to think about how JUnit scans for classes — does it discover both top-level and nested classes? If I have a static nested class inside another test class, will JUnit find it in the classpath? It seems Jupiter might pick up static member classes, but perhaps not nested ones unless they're annotated with @Nested. To cover all bases, I could create a separate top-level class packaged privately. I also need to consider class visibility and annotations, especially when using @ParameterizedClass.
